It's called the sump plate (left). The 914 replacement is called the
taco plate (right):

On May 2, 2007, at 8:43 PM, Zack Jarrett wrote:

> The final post, from Colin, the itinerant air cooled mechanic
> himself, is as follows:
>
> "It just requires a little futzing to keep things centered as you
> gently persuade the red ring to expand against the case hole as it
> rolls around the bevelled edge of the taco plate. If it goes
> crokked, back off a bit on the 10mm bolts and go at it again.  Colin"

Red silicone swells over time from contact with oil.

The correct solution is to replace the gasket. If you don't have a
new one, get one.

